FBIS3-16273 "drsov050_b_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Stepashin Hospitalized After Meeting Yeltsin MK1503101094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 15 Mar 94 p 1 MK1503101094 Moscow SEGODNYA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [POSTFACTUM report: "Federal Counterintelligence Service Director Sergey Stepashin Hospitalized"] [Text] Lieutenant General Sergey Stepashin, Federal Counterintelligence Service director, was taken to the hospital in an ambulance from his own office after, according to some information, becoming sick due to a worsening of his stomach ulcer. The confidential source, who would rather remain anonymous, intimated that the reason was not the illness but the meeting with President Yeltsin, soon after which Sergey Stepashin was sent to the departmental hospital.
